1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper presents an algorithm for segmentation of the inner and outer boundary of thoracic and abdominal aortic aneurysms in computed tomography angiography (CTA) acquisitions. This involves image processing and analysis techniques commonly used in computer vision.
2. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper deals with the monitoring of thoracic and abdominal aortic aneurysm stents, which involves mechanical engineering principles and techniques.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions the use of an adapted active contour model approach, which is a machine learning technique commonly used in image segmentation.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper involves the processing and analysis of multimedia data in the form of CTA images.
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper involves the use of numerical methods and algorithms for the segmentation and measurement of aneurysm size.
